Since most evenly paced races put you at the back of the pack of racers,<div>You become the "run from behind" (sit and kick) type of racer.</div><div>That "tactic" is visual, you can SEE it.</div><div>You can't see even pace.</div><div>So you get lulled into "run from behind" (sit and kick) until you are in the race where that doesn't&nbsp;work.</div><div>As I said before, when a race goes out SLOW,&nbsp;it goes badly. &nbsp;You never want to&nbsp;do THAT again.</div>